<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued February 23 at 3:08AM CST until February 24 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM THIS MORNING TO
6 PM CST THURSDAY...
* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total combined sleet and
snow accumulations of up to eight tenths of an inch, and ice
accumulations of a light glaze.
* WHERE...Hardeman, Foard and Knox Counties.
* WHEN...From 6 AM Wednesday to 6 PM CST Thursday.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.
For the latest road conditions call 800 4 5 2 9 2 9 2 for road
information.</instruction>
